{"id": "QmaSGxr7sxVkAwQGqadpcGgemAAuj8k6Ph3JHCcRX1wpGq", "title": "Peg Restoration Mechanism", "body": "Over the past few weeks we\u2019ve made changes to the way the staking contract works to prevent people purchasing debt and instead minting it. While it has worked to some extent, the peg is still trading at a premium and users are facing impermanent loss when unsticking their debt.\n\nThis issue isn\u2019t unique to ARC and faced by most synthetic stable coins such as sUSD and DAI due to the fact that there\u2019s no supply sink when external demand spikes due to Yield Farming or other unexpected use cases. In order to combat this the Maker community has extensively discussed the idea of \u201cpeg restoration mechanisms\u201d but ultimately opted against it due to the idea of \u201ctaxing\u201d DAI holders doesn\u2019t align with the vision.\n\nARC is facing the same issue but we\u2019re still young as a community and have the boundaries to experiment given the scale of the project at the moment. The proposal below is the first step in working towards implementing a peg restoration mechanism which helps regulate the peg while providing an additional revenue source for ARC holders. \n\nIf we can successfully experiment with a manual peg restoration mechanism, we can then move to design an automated peg restoration mechanism without manual human intervention. The implications of getting this right are very large for ARC.\n\n\u2014\n\nHere\u2019s how it would work:\n\n1. The admin key is used to call `addMinter(address)` on the LINKUSD token contract. The passed address will be an EOA.\n\n2. The newly added EOA then calls `mint(amount)` on the LINKUSD contract\n\n3. The EOA then goes to Balancer and sells the minted amount of LINKUSD for USDC restoring the balance of the pool. USDC received from this trade is not touched or moved around.\n\n4. When the price of LINKUSD goes below $0.95, a new community proposal is used to initiate a buy back of the debt with the USDC sold. The profit from the arbitrage transaction is then given back to ARC Token Holders as revenue.\n\n\u2014\n\nAs of the time of writing this proposal, the Balancer pool has the following quantities of tokens:\n\n105.8k LINKUSD\n123.5k USDC\n\nBy voting yes on this proposal, the EOA would mint the difference in the pool (at the time of execution) and then sell it on Balancer. \n\nBy voting no, the proposal will be rejected.\n\nTO CLARIFY: If this is successful we will focus on building an automated version of this mechanism and avoid using admin keys.\n\n\u2014\n\nFurther reading resources about peg restoration mechanisms:\n\n- https://insights.deribit.com/market-research/the-future-of-money-could-be-discretionary/\n\n- https://forum.makerdao.com/t/negative-interest-rates/842", "choices": ["Yes, mint LINKUSD to help restore the peg", "No, let LINKUSD free-float"], "start": 1600819200, "end": 1600905600, "snapshot": "10922000", "state": "closed", "author": "0xFEC18996C36D02902E4c55bcFB7A1c73AA1500Cd", "space": {"id": "arckyf", "name": "ARC KYF Voting"}, "votes": 40, "votes_data": [{"id": "QmTjHCWz1uTf9BmeUz7URDCrTotR9oXZnQzz1LD53tzRLd", "voter": "0x554B1Bd47B7d180844175cA4635880da8A3c70B9", "created": 1600887134, "choice": 1, "space": {"id": "arckyf"}}, {"id": "QmRd1maxKL8Zk4hPY3orJyiLCpdEtcyPfNDbpHtLDZKjDR", "voter": "0x98e7D41CB1822Fc5e86F41C0290561cfFCF87e99", "created": 1600882172, "choice": 1, "space": {"id": "arckyf"}}, {"id": "QmPYQokbpksktuqALkfDfLW4mWWcToiNmMU2KHJsJU4dZs", "voter": "0xb90781Ceb500f80A9c101225eD5451449a3Aa5bc", "created": 1600879054, "choice": 1, "space": {"id": "arckyf"}}, {"id": "QmPCREe1wmoJmBCxK2nPM1WBvyVp5EqtF6c87kF4exBTCS", "voter": "0x564a77fE6ec7377e6C153D7E2E23029067073eFF", "created": 1600878076, "choice": 1, "space": {"id": "arckyf"}}, {"id": "QmcgJvASVbjAc74xmMd7DvvhVRfseznreE5WTiqjgzWjSL", "voter": "0x569d4C513673F8A611Cf4DDE30563498642a8579", "created": 1600875867, "choice": 1, "space": {"id": "arckyf"}}, {"id": "QmUKv97JqJV